They have reasonably priced meals too! --------------------------------------------------------------------- UPDATE: Chavez Restaurant has added some delicious steak empanadas to its menu offering that come close to tasting like a Brazilian steak in a pie crust. I hear they can also make Chile Rellenos empanadas upon request (when they have the perfect chiles on hand). This place continues to step up it's game. --------------------------------------------------------------------- Super Update!! They are now making delicious Cuban Sandwiches! And out of this world Tortilla Soup!! Stop in on Cinco de Mayo. The menu will be fantastic. --------------------------------------------------------------------- Extraordinary Update: Chavez Restaurant just added an all-you can-eat buffet. 10am-3pm Saturdays and Sundays only. $10 a person. I love this place!!!  I cannot get enough of the MENUDO. The scent of the food wafts down the street,  and I wake up craving it every morning. I moved to Chicago from California 16 years ago and have been seeking the perfect menudo since 2002. Here we are in 2019, and luckily,  I can walk to this restaurant and eat here whenever I want.   Everyone is nice,  courteous and always smiling.  The food is fresh and authentic.  Try this place and you'll never regret it.  You'll be hooked,  but you'll never regret it! <3

We frequently dine here because of the quick service and consistently tasty food options. Steak tacos are spot on, I always go for Mexican style with onions and cilantro. Dinners are always served on unique colorful large plates which is a step above most that usually toss food in a basket. Chicken enchiladas are another go to for us, beautifully presented and nicely flavored. I'm super critical and picky when it comes to Mexican restaurants, if there was any red flag here I wouldn't return, but I keep coming back!

I order a rice water and they didn't put any straws. I understand when it gets busy we can forget,but when I showed up at the restaurant  there was no one in the restaurant.

Friendly owner but that's about it. The food was pretty good when they 1st opened noticed cooks change quite often. They're never consistent with the taste. Unfortunately   Today has been the last of my visits sad to say because I live so close but I'd rather travel for a good mexican meal for the price's they charge. Today my 1st disappointment was opening my take out bag to see I was only given 1 red sauce and 1 green sauce for 6 tacos and a burrito! Like really!? Must we have to share one small container of hot sauce? 2nd the steak was very very salty 3rd the steak tacos were dry. My review is not to knock them down or stir customers away but hopefully it'll be to better the business. Best of luck!

When they opened they had decent food but like many Mexican restaurants after a month or so they stopped serving good food. The food there is terrible this place will not make it don't even try it. They are even shorting people's take out orders. Very disappointed that they desided to serve bad food to the people that supported them at first now they just don't care if your food taste terrible.
Wow I love the chicken burrito very delicious best food in town,We will definitely return. Outstanding horchata Thanks Chavez for the best food in town.

So disappointing! We went there when they just opened-and everything was awesome. Today-what a joke. I ordered take out. They didn't put guacamole to my appetizer though it was listed on the menu. Portion got smaller. Burrito was all sour cream and lettuce almost no meat. They didn't give us any salsa, not even one! I ordered large horchata they gave me whole cup of ice (I asked no ice) the lady was so unhappy to replace my order. Will never be returning again - they will be out of business in no time, quite empty there already.
